transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling customer service, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, I placed an order last night.

Speaker 1: I was trying to see what medication they described to me.

Speaker 2: Okay, name and birthday?

Speaker 1: Lloyd Briggs, 4-29-1960.

Speaker 2: They gave you Viagra?

Speaker 1: Is that the new one?

Speaker 2: Uh, let me see.

Speaker 1: No, you want the new one?

Speaker 2: Yeah, if it wasn't the new one, I already had old.

Speaker 1: Okay, let me have this so she can check in.

Speaker 2: The new one is A-some-A-B-C or something?

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: Yeah, that's the one I was calling for.

Speaker 1: Okay, give me a second.

Speaker 2: Okay, I switched it to the new one.

Speaker 1: Okay, and that will be mailed to them?

Speaker 2: Yes, that will be mailed to them.

Speaker 1: Yes, if it ain't the new one, I already got that old one.

Speaker 2: Okay, no problem.

Speaker 1: Okay, was there anything else I can assist you with?

Speaker 2: No, I just wanted to make sure that I was getting the right one.

Speaker 1: Yes, sir.

Speaker 2: You're a good sir.

Speaker 1: All right, I appreciate it.

Speaker 2: You're welcome.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
